 <text id="B0773T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>Jackson forwards ration request reports to McDonnell in Winchester.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R F &amp; A L</abbr>
     <lb/>Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist</abbr> Augusta &amp; Highland
     <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> John A McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr
       expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr</abbr>
     </name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1867-05-10">May 10/67</date>
      <name type="place">Winchester</name>
     </dateline>

     <salute>Captain</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>I have the honor to acknowledge receipt of communication from your <abbr expan="Headquarters"
       >H<hi rend="super">d</hi> Q<hi rend="super">r</hi></abbr> May 7/67 authorizing me to forward
     Ration estimates for May and referring me to "Circular 33 <abbr expan="Headquarters">H<hi
       rend="super">d</hi> Q<hi rend="super">rs</hi></abbr>
     <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr</abbr>
     <abbr expan="Series">S.</abbr> 1866" The office file of orders at this post is so imperfect as
     to be almost useless and <unclear>much</unclear> was <unclear>missing</unclear>. I respectfully
     transmit Ration returns for 21 days calling for 630 rations. These lack my signature as I was
     instructed to forward them some time back. If incorrect in this report or if you require the
     names please inform me.</p>

    <closer>
     <salute>
      <abbr expan="Your obedient servant">Yr. obt servt</abbr>
     </salute>
     <signed><hi rend="underline">Tho<hi rend="super">s</hi> P Jackson</hi><lb/>Agent</signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
